outcomes.title: Recognize proportionality
outcomes.description:
Express relationships of direct and
                inverse proportionality.
outcomes.template:
Suppose {{lhs}} is {{kindly}} proportional to {{prompt}}. Write an equation that expresses this relationship.

{{lhs}} = {{rhs}}

outcomes.title: Find units of slope of linear model
outcomes.description: Determine the units of the slope of a linear model.
outcomes.template:
Suppose the quantities {{ind}}, measured in {{ind_units}} and {{dep}}, measured in {{dep_units}}, are related by the linear model {{lhs}} = {{rhs}}.

What are the units of the slope of this model?

{{dep_units}}/{{ind_units}}

outcomes.title: Find linear model from two points
outcomes.description:
Find the slope and y-intercept of a linear model
                given two points on the line.
outcomes.template:
Suppose that {{x}} and {{y}} are related by a linear model and that when {{x}} = {{x1}}, {{y}} = {{y1}}, and that when {{x}} = {{x2}}, {{y}} = {{y2}}. Find the slope and y-intercept of the model.

The slope is {{slope}} and the y-intercept is {{intercept}}.
